    "When we disaggregate the representations by men, we see topics relating to God with the highest frequency, then superheroes; urinating; drinking beer; Viagra; and reading books.",
    "Much of these findings are not present in current academic research and again this is an interesting and novel discovery, presenting unknown harms in downstream tasks (see Fig. 3).",
    "Figure 4 provides random excerpts for context.In contrast, prompts including men, the top 2 topics represent 56% of the outputs of the top 15 topics, intersecting with God and superheroes-stark contrast to the degrading and harmful content generated for women.",
